SEC. 6.

Powers and Functions of the Commission.

â The Commission shall, at all times, act with transparency and dispatch and shall have, among others, the following powers and functions;

Approve, amend, renew or deny any license, registration or certificate issued under this Code;

Fix and assess fees and/or charges as it may find reasonable in the exercise of regulation;

Regulate, supervise and monitor the operations and management of pre-need companies to ensure compliance with the provisions of this Code, existing laws, rules and regulations including, but not limited to:

Revoking or nullifying investments made and/or entered into by a pre-need company or a trustee which are contrary to existing laws, rules and regulations;

Demanding for the conversion of the investments made by the trustee to cash or other liquid assets to protect the interest of the planholders; and

Regulating, investigating or supervising activities of pre-need companies, their officers, employees, sales counselors, consultants or agents;

Issue cease and desist orders to prevent fraud and injury to the investing public;

